[2026-03-09T23:47:17Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HZBeDkFazZ2Q3rECpyV5W6","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the log viewer component. Let me create a summary of my findings.\n\n## Summary: Log Viewer Component in Cloche Web Portal\n\nI have conducted a thorough search of the log viewer component in the web portal. Here are the key findings:\n\n### 1. **Log Display Structure (Accordion-like)**\n\nThe log viewer uses a **step-based accordion pattern** where:\n\n- Steps are displayed in a clickable table (`runs-table`) in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n- Each step row shows: Step Name, Result (badge), Started time, Duration\n- Clicking a step row toggles the visibility of an \"output row\" below it\n- The output row contains a scrollable `<pre class=\"step-output\">` that displays step-specific log output\n- The main log viewer is a separate scrollable container (`#log-viewer`) that shows unified logs\n\n**Related files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` (lines 43-60 for steps table, 62-66 for main log viewer)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (lines 154-168 for step output styling)\n\n### 2. **SSE (Server-Sent Events) Handling**\n\nThe log streaming uses **Server-Sent Events** for real-time updates:\n\n- **Endpoint**: `/api/runs/{id}/stream` (defined in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`, lines 135, 665-731)\n- **Handler function**: `handleAPIStream()` implements both:\n  - **Active runs**: Subscribe to live broadcaster and stream events in real-time\n  - **Completed runs**: Serve archived `full.log` file\n- **Event types**: \n  - `data: ` events contain JSON `LogLine` objects with `{timestamp, type, content}`\n  - `event: done` signals stream completion\n- **Log parsing**: Claude stream JSON is parsed from raw JSON into human-readable text using `ParseClaudeStream()` and `ParseClaudeLine()`\n\n**Related files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 665-731 for SSE handler)\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` (LogLine struct definition at lines 7-12)\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go` (Claude JSON parsing logic)\n\n### 3. **HTML Templates and JavaScript**\n\n**Main template**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n\n**Log viewer JavaScript logic** (lines 70-237):\n- Creates EventSource connection to `/api/runs/{runID}/stream`\n- `appendLogLine()` function creates colored span elements for each log line based on type\n- Auto-scroll behavior: tracks scroll position and auto-scrolls if user is at bottom\n- Event handling:\n  - `onmessage`: parses JSON LogLine and appends to DOM\n  - `done` event: closes connection and marks as complete\n  - `onerror`: handles connection errors\n\n**Step output accordion** (lines 212-236):\n- Click event listener on `.step-row` elements\n- Toggles visibility of corresponding `#output-{index}` row\n- Lazy-loads step output via `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n- Supports filtering by log type: `type=script` or `type=llm`\n\n**Active run polling** (lines 126-180):\n- For running workflows, polls `/api/runs/{id}` every 2 seconds\n- Updates steps table and container status dynamically\n- Reloads page if run state changes\n\n### 4. **State Management**\n\nThe component uses **minimal client-side state**:\n\n- `runState`: initial run state from server\n- `runID`: from template context\n- `autoScroll`: boolean tracking user scroll position\n- `logContent`: DOM reference to pre element containing all log lines\n- No persistent state store or complex framework; uses vanilla JavaScript with fetch API\n\n**Broadcaster (server-side)**:\n- `Broadcaster` type in `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` (lines 32-139)\n- Manages active run subscriptions with thread-safe map\n- `Subscribe()`, `Publish()`, `Finish()`, `Unsubscribe()` methods\n- Buffers 256 log lines per subscriber\n- Non-blocking publish: drops lines if subscriber is slow\n\n### 5. **Key Files Summary**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | HTTP handlers (SSE endpoint, log parsing, log file serving) |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` | Log viewer UI and JavaScript logic |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` | Styling for log viewer, steps table, badges |\n| `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` | LogLine struct and run broadcaster implementation |\n| `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go` | Claude stream JSON parsing utilities |\n| `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` | Log writer that creates full.log files |\n\n### 6. **Log File Format**\n\nLogs are stored in `{projectDir}/.cloche/{runID}/output/full.log`:\n```\n[2026-03-03T10:15:00Z] [status] step_started: build\n[2026-03-03T10:15:01Z] [script] npm run build\n[2026-03-03T10:15:02Z] [llm] Claude: Starting analysis\n```\n\nLines are parsed by regex in `parseFullLogLine()` to extract timestamp, type, and content."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a95a23b3f98b35903 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 57400\ntool_uses: 17\nduration_ms: 33915</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"614f74a0-ca83-4717-850e-1a3f0c809f5e","uuid":"18269a54-e897-49cc-8a9e-4a7daf3ecab7","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find the log viewer component in the web portal. Look in internal/adapters/web/ and related directories. I need to understand:\n1. How logs are displayed (accordion structure)\n2. How SSE events are handled\n3. The HTML templates and JavaScript involved\n4. Any existing state management\n\nSearch thoroughly for files related to: log viewer, accordion, SSE, templates, JavaScript in the web portal.","agentId":"a95a23b3f98b35903","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the log viewer component. Let me create a summary of my findings.\n\n## Summary: Log Viewer Component in Cloche Web Portal\n\nI have conducted a thorough search of the log viewer component in the web portal. Here are the key findings:\n\n### 1. **Log Display Structure (Accordion-like)**\n\nThe log viewer uses a **step-based accordion pattern** where:\n\n- Steps are displayed in a clickable table (`runs-table`) in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n- Each step row shows: Step Name, Result (badge), Started time, Duration\n- Clicking a step row toggles the visibility of an \"output row\" below it\n- The output row contains a scrollable `<pre class=\"step-output\">` that displays step-specific log output\n- The main log viewer is a separate scrollable container (`#log-viewer`) that shows unified logs\n\n**Related files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` (lines 43-60 for steps table, 62-66 for main log viewer)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (lines 154-168 for step output styling)\n\n### 2. **SSE (Server-Sent Events) Handling**\n\nThe log streaming uses **Server-Sent Events** for real-time updates:\n\n- **Endpoint**: `/api/runs/{id}/stream` (defined in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`, lines 135, 665-731)\n- **Handler function**: `handleAPIStream()` implements both:\n  - **Active runs**: Subscribe to live broadcaster and stream events in real-time\n  - **Completed runs**: Serve archived `full.log` file\n- **Event types**: \n  - `data: ` events contain JSON `LogLine` objects with `{timestamp, type, content}`\n  - `event: done` signals stream completion\n- **Log parsing**: Claude stream JSON is parsed from raw JSON into human-readable text using `ParseClaudeStream()` and `ParseClaudeLine()`\n\n**Related files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 665-731 for SSE handler)\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` (LogLine struct definition at lines 7-12)\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go` (Claude JSON parsing logic)\n\n### 3. **HTML Templates and JavaScript**\n\n**Main template**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n\n**Log viewer JavaScript logic** (lines 70-237):\n- Creates EventSource connection to `/api/runs/{runID}/stream`\n- `appendLogLine()` function creates colored span elements for each log line based on type\n- Auto-scroll behavior: tracks scroll position and auto-scrolls if user is at bottom\n- Event handling:\n  - `onmessage`: parses JSON LogLine and appends to DOM\n  - `done` event: closes connection and marks as complete\n  - `onerror`: handles connection errors\n\n**Step output accordion** (lines 212-236):\n- Click event listener on `.step-row` elements\n- Toggles visibility of corresponding `#output-{index}` row\n- Lazy-loads step output via `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n- Supports filtering by log type: `type=script` or `type=llm`\n\n**Active run polling** (lines 126-180):\n- For running workflows, polls `/api/runs/{id}` every 2 seconds\n- Updates steps table and container status dynamically\n- Reloads page if run state changes\n\n### 4. **State Management**\n\nThe component uses **minimal client-side state**:\n\n- `runState`: initial run state from server\n- `runID`: from template context\n- `autoScroll`: boolean tracking user scroll position\n- `logContent`: DOM reference to pre element containing all log lines\n- No persistent state store or complex framework; uses vanilla JavaScript with fetch API\n\n**Broadcaster (server-side)**:\n- `Broadcaster` type in `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` (lines 32-139)\n- Manages active run subscriptions with thread-safe map\n- `Subscribe()`, `Publish()`, `Finish()`, `Unsubscribe()` methods\n- Buffers 256 log lines per subscriber\n- Non-blocking publish: drops lines if subscriber is slow\n\n### 5. **Key Files Summary**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | HTTP handlers (SSE endpoint, log parsing, log file serving) |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` | Log viewer UI and JavaScript logic |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` | Styling for log viewer, steps table, badges |\n| `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` | LogLine struct and run broadcaster implementation |\n| `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go` | Claude stream JSON parsing utilities |\n| `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` | Log writer that creates full.log files |\n\n### 6. **Log File Format**\n\nLogs are stored in `{projectDir}/.cloche/{runID}/output/full.log`:\n```\n[2026-03-03T10:15:00Z] [status] step_started: build\n[2026-03-03T10:15:01Z] [script] npm run build\n[2026-03-03T10:15:02Z] [llm] Claude: Starting analysis\n```\n\nLines are parsed by regex in `parseFullLogLine()` to extract timestamp, type, and content."}],"totalDurationMs":33915,"totalTokens":57400,"totalToolUseCount":17,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":750,"cache_read_input_tokens":55286,"output_tokens":1364,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":750},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
